02/11/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- According to the latest poll conducted by the daily Vecernji List and published last weekend, incumbent Stipe Mesic enjoys the highest public support among candidates running for president. Mesic was backed by 57.4 per cent of the respondents. Ten days ago, his popularity was 54.2 per cent. His main rival, War Veterans Minister Jadranka Kosor of the ruling HDZ party, was supported by 18.6 per cent of those polled, compared to 17.9 per cent in the previous survey. The elections are expected early next year. (HINA - 31/10/04; Vecernji list - 30/10/04)
